  "text": "The Kafka ProduceRequest network write chain traces from the KafkaProducer client through the network layer to the broker's log append. Here is the complete call sequence:\n\nPRODUCER CLIENT SIDE:\n\n1. KafkaProducer.send() (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/KafkaProducer.java) - Public API that accepts ProducerRecord\n\n2. KafkaProducer.doSend() (line 974) - Internal implementation that serializes key/value, determines partition, and calls accumulator.append()\n   - Line 1029: accumulator.append(record.topic(), partition, timestamp, serializedKey, serializedValue, headers, appendCallbacks, remainingWaitMs, nowMs, cluster)\n\n3. RecordAccumulator.append() (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/internals/RecordAccumulator.java, line 275) - Batches records for efficient network transmission\n   - Allocates buffers and organizes records by partition\n   - Returns RecordAppendResult with future for tracking completion\n\n4. Sender.sendProducerData() (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/internals/Sender.java, line 357) - Background thread method\n   - Drains batches from accumulator using accumulator.drain() at line 395\n   - Calls sendProduceRequests(batches, now) at line 442\n\n5. Sender.sendProduceRequests() (line 856) - Iterates over batches grouped by broker node\n   - Calls sendProduceRequest() for each broker destination\n\n6. Sender.sendProduceRequest() (line 864) - Creates ProduceRequest from batches\n   - Line 914: client.send(clientRequest, now) - Sends request to NetworkClient\n\n7. NetworkClient.send() (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/NetworkClient.java, line 541) - Async network send\n   - Calls doSend(request, false, now)\n   - doSend builds the request and serializes it\n   - Line 617: selector.send(new NetworkSend(clientRequest.destination(), send)) - Sends to socket\n\nBROKER SERVER SIDE:\n\n8. ReplicaManager.appendRecords() (core/src/main/scala/kafka/server/ReplicaManager.scala, line 674) - Entry point for produce request\n   - Line 688: appendRecordsToLeader() - Appends to leader replicas\n\n9. ReplicaManager.appendRecordsToLeader() (line 627) - Appends records to local leader log\n   - Line 637: appendToLocalLog() - Performs actual append operations\n\n10. ReplicaManager.appendToLocalLog() (line 1370) - Maps over partitions and performs appends\n    - Line 1408: partition.appendRecordsToLeader(records, origin, requiredAcks, requestLocal, verificationGuards) - Per-partition append\n\n11. Partition.appendRecordsToLeader() (core/src/main/scala/kafka/cluster/Partition.scala, line 1361) - Partition-level append\n    - Line 1376: leaderLog.appendAsLeader(records, this.leaderEpoch, origin, requestLocal, verificationGuard) - Delegates to log\n\n12. UnifiedLog.appendAsLeader() (storage/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/storage/internals/log/UnifiedLog.java, line 1024) - Log append with leader semantics\n    - Line 1030: append() - Core append method\n\n13. UnifiedLog.append() (line 1081) - Performs actual log append to disk\n    - Validates and assigns offsets\n    - Trims invalid bytes\n    - Writes to log segment files\n\nThis call chain represents the complete flow from a producer's send() call through batching, network transmission, to the broker receiving the request and appending records to the partition log."
